350 2631 IOStatus DBImpl::CreateAndNewDirectory(
351 FileSystem* fs, const std::string& dirname,
352 std::unique_ptr<FSDirectory>* directory) {
353 // We call CreateDirIfMissing() as the directory may already exist (if we
354 // are reopening a DB), when this happens we don't want creating the
355 // directory to cause an error. However, we need to check if creating the
356 // directory fails or else we may get an obscure message about the lock
